Judge Neil Gorsuch has begun confirmation hearings at the United States Senate for his nomination as a Supreme Court Justice. President Donald J. Trump has selected Gorsuch as his choice for this position, praising him as the most qualified and principled defender of the Constitution. Gorsuch follows the same approach as Justice Scalia, closely adhering to statutory text and the original meaning of the Constitution. He has written opinions that identify fundamental issues in existing legal doctrines, demonstrating his ability to question prior decisions and restore traditional legal principles. Gorsuch has an impressive educational background, with degrees from Columbia University, Harvard Law School, and Oxford University. He has also served in various positions at the U.S. Department of Justice. Overall, Gorsuch is considered highly qualified for the Supreme Court and is seen as a suitable selection to carry on the legacy of the late Justice Antonin Scalia.